name: cis-4-cyclohexene-1,2-dicarboxylic anhydride
Reason: 4-Cyclohexene-1,2-dicarboxylic anhydride has a melting point influenced by functional groups relative to the base melting point of benzene, which is around 5°C. The cyclohexene group itself contributes to the melting point due to increased molecular weight and van der Waals interactions, estimated at around +20°C. The carboxylic acid and anhydride functionalities introduce additional rigid structures that can participate in dipole interactions and potentially hydrogen bonding, raising the melting point by approximately +30°C. The presence of two phenyl groups can also contribute to the melting point due to increased molecular weight and van der Waals interactions, estimated at around +20°C per group, totaling +40°C.
